5 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
6 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
7 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a Statewide
8 Recovery Special Account for the Department of Human Services for
9 each appropriation section of this act. The duration of such
10 accounts shall continue for the period of time that monies related
11 to the American Rescue Plan Act of 2021 are being budgeted,
12 expended, or managed in the state. The ending of such period shall
13 be determined by the State Treasurer, and shall result in the
14 closing of such accounts as a matter of law. Such accounts shall be
15 continuing accounts as otherwise provided in this section, not
16 subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall exclusively consist of
17 monies related to the relevant appropriations made in this act and
18 as otherwise directed by law. All monies deposited to the credit of
19 such accounts are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and
20 expended by the Department of Human Services in accordance with the
21 provisions of this act. Expenditures from such accounts shall be
22 made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims
23 filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
24 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
